Female genitalia
(
Figs 2G–2J
). Segment VI with thin spur ventrally. Corners of tergum and sternum of segment VII rounded in outline. Segment VIII cone shaped. Segments IX, X, XI (
Fig. 2H
) often retracted into segment VIII or VII and VIII (
Fig. 2G
). Segment IX membranous, trapezoidal, indistinguishable from the intersegmental membrane VIII–X, proximal part slightly wider than distal edge. Segment X cylindrical. Segment XI with pair of cerci (c.). Apodemal rods from segment VIII (ap.r.VIII) extend forward to segment VII. Apodemal rods from segment XI (ap.r.XI) extending forward to segment VI or VII. Posterior process of vaginal apparatus (p.pr.) in dorsal view long elliptical with apex slightly incised (
Fig. 2I
), in lateral view elongate bar shaped (
Fig. 2J
).
